sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Cli as Client
    participant O as Origin · append handler
    participant R as Redis · stream slot
    participant WS as wake_stream · durable
    participant W as Worker pool
    Cli->>O: POST /events/abc + body
    O->>R: append.lua — ZADD frame · HSET tail · PUBLISH ds:notify (one atomic script)
    O-->>Cli: 204 · the byte is committed
    Note over O: OnStreamAppend fires in-process on this origin — event-driven, no timer
    O->>R: StreamSubscribers — read the fan-out index for this path
    O->>WS: AppendWakeEvent — a durable {type wake} event, the outbox record
    O->>R: RecordWakeEventSent — mark wake_event_sent_ns, fenced
    W->>WS: tail the wake_stream and claim the wake
    W->>R: ack.lua — cursor advances to tail
    Note over R: the recovery sweep fires nothing here — it re-emits only a wake a crash left unsent
